race.comment: INKAANTOON (10) comes across from Victoria and lines up here on the fresh side. She pulled up with an issue before being sold, but her runs prior on heavy decks were sound. Back on top of the ground today and back to an easier race looks a recipe for success. PANCHO'S PLACE (12) is on debut for the Harding stable after being prepped up by Mack Hall in town. His trials have been solid coming into this and he'll carry no weight after the claim of Tsang. Looks to have found a suitable race for him to make an immediate impact. CAP CAVOUR (2) is first-up today and was placed fresh last campaign at Ascot over 1000m. The inside draw should see him close to the speed and he can resume on a positive note for the new stable. GEORGE ON SKATES (5) is better than we saw last time out and can bounce back to his prior form. I HAD A DREAM (1) is in the mix first-up from a good gate.
